IF.IFdes:
Story 1: Emma
Hi! My name is Emma. I am 20 years old. I am from England, but I live in London. I study at university. My favorite hobbies are painting and playing the guitar. I also love walking in the park with my dog. On weekends, I go to the library to read books.

Story 2: Jack
Hello, I’m Jack. I am 25 years old. I live in New York City. I work as a photographer. I enjoy taking pictures of nature and people. In my free time, I like cycling and watching movies. My dream is to travel the world and take photos of new places.

Story 3: Sofia
Hi, I’m Sofia. I am 18 years old. I live in Madrid, Spain. I am a high school student. I love dancing and listening to music. My favorite band is Coldplay. I also enjoy spending time with my friends at the coffee shop near my house.

Story 4: Tom
Hi there! My name is Tom. I am 30 years old. I live in Sydney, Australia. I am a chef, and I love cooking new dishes. In my free time, I enjoy surfing at the beach and playing football with my friends. My goal is to open my own restaurant one day.

seo.metaTitle: Talking About Your Family (Nói về gia đình)
seo.metaDescription: Thực sử dụng các mẫu câu đơn giản để hỏi và trả lời.

IF.IFname: Talking About Your Family (Nói về gia đình)
IF.IFdes:
Story 1: Alice
Hi! My name is Alice. I live with my parents and my younger sister. My dad is an engineer, and my mom is a nurse. My sister is 10 years old, and she loves painting. Every evening, we eat dinner together. On weekends, we watch movies or play games at home. My family is very close.

Story 2: Ben
Hello, I’m Ben. My family has five people: my parents, my two brothers, and me. My father works in an office, and my mother is a teacher. My older brother is at university, and my younger brother is in high school. We often play football together in the park on Sundays.

Story 3: Clara
Hi, I’m Clara. I live with my grandparents, my mom, and my little brother. My grandfather is retired, but he loves gardening. My grandmother likes to bake cakes. My mom works in a hospital. My brother is 8 years old and enjoys playing with his toys. We spend a lot of time together.

Story 4: John
Hi there! My name is John. I come from a small family. It’s just me and my mom. My mom is a chef, and she works in a big restaurant. She makes delicious food, and I love helping her at home. On weekends, we visit my aunt and her kids. Family time is very special to me.

IF.IFdes:
Spring
Hi! My name is Emma. In spring, I wake up at 6:30 AM. The weather is fresh and cool, so I open my window and enjoy it. After breakfast, I water the flowers in my garden. In the afternoon, I study at home and take a short walk outside. At night, I watch TV with my family and go to bed at 10:00 PM.

Summer
Hello, I’m Emma. Summer is my favorite season. I wake up at 6:00 AM and go swimming in the morning. After that, I eat fruit and rest. In the afternoon, I read books or listen to music. The weather is very hot, so I drink cold juice. At night, I sleep with the fan on and dream about traveling to the beach.

Autumn
Hi, I’m Emma. In autumn, I wake up at 7:00 AM. I eat breakfast and ride my bike to the park. The leaves are orange and yellow, and the weather is cool. I love walking and taking pictures of the trees. In the afternoon, I write in my journal and drink hot tea. I go to bed early because the days are shorter.

Winter
Hello, I’m Emma. Winter is very cold, so I wake up at 8:00 AM. I drink hot chocolate to warm up. After breakfast, I sit by the fireplace and read books. In the afternoon, I wear warm clothes and go outside for a walk. At night, I enjoy dinner with my family and sleep under a thick blanket.

seo.metaTitle: Shopping and Asking for Prices (Mua sắm và hỏi giá cả)
seo.metaDescription: Thực sử dụng các mẫu câu đơn giản để hỏi và trả lời.

IF.IFname: Shopping and Asking for Prices (Mua sắm và hỏi giá cả)
IF.IFdes:
Story 1: The Clothing Store
Hi, I’m Emma. Today, I go to a clothing store to buy a new dress. I see a red dress and ask, “How much is this dress?” The shop assistant says, “It’s $30.” I try it on, and it fits perfectly. I ask, “Can I pay with my card?” The assistant says, “Yes, you can.” I pay for the dress and thank her.

Story 2: The Shoe Shop
Hello, I’m Emma. I need new shoes for walking. At the shoe shop, I ask, “Do you have size 38?” The salesperson says, “Yes, we do. They are $50.” I try them on and ask, “Do you have these in black?” The salesperson finds black shoes for me. I like them, so I buy them with cash.

Story 3: The Supermarket
Hi, I’m Emma. I go to the supermarket to buy some fruit. I ask the staff, “How much are the bananas?” She says, “They are $2 per kilo.” I say, “I’ll take 3 kilos, please.” At the checkout, I give cash and get my change. The bananas look fresh, and I am happy with my shopping.

Story 4: The Electronics Store
Hello, I’m Emma. I need a new phone charger. At the electronics store, I ask, “How much is this charger?” The salesperson says, “It’s $20.” I ask, “Do you have a cheaper one?” He shows me another charger for $15. I decide to buy the cheaper one. I pay with my card and leave the store.

seo.metaTitle: Talking About Hobbies and Free Time (Nói về sở thích và thời gian rảnh)
seo.metaDescription: Thực sử dụng các mẫu câu đơn giản để hỏi và trả lời.

IF.IFname: Talking About Hobbies and Free Time (Nói về sở thích và thời gian rảnh)
IF.IFdes:
Story 1: Mom
Hi, I’m Emma’s mom. In my free time, I love gardening. I enjoy planting flowers and vegetables in the backyard. It makes me happy to see my plants grow. Sometimes, I listen to music while I work in the garden. On weekends, I also enjoy baking cakes for my family.

Story 2: Dad
Hello, I’m Emma’s dad. I like fishing in my free time. On Saturday mornings, I go to the river with my fishing gear. I enjoy the quiet and fresh air. Sometimes, I catch a big fish and bring it home for dinner. Fishing helps me relax after a busy week.

Story 3: Brother
Hi, I’m Emma’s brother. I enjoy playing video games in my free time. I like racing games the most. I play with my friends online, and we have so much fun. When I am not gaming, I ride my bike around the park. Riding makes me feel free and happy.

Story 4: Grandma
Hello, I’m Emma’s grandma. I love knitting in my free time. I make sweaters, scarves, and hats for my family. Knitting is relaxing and keeps me busy. Sometimes, I also enjoy reading books about history. In the evening, I watch TV shows with my grandchildren. They make me laugh.

IF.IFdes:
Story 1: Paris
Hi, I’m Emma. I visit Paris for the first time. I want to see the Eiffel Tower. I ask a passerby, “Excuse me, how can I get to the Eiffel Tower?” He says, “Take the metro, line 6, and get off at Trocadéro station.” I thank him and follow the directions. The Eiffel Tower is amazing!

Story 2: New York City
Hello, I’m Emma. In New York, I need to find Central Park. I ask a police officer, “Where is Central Park?” He says, “It’s straight ahead, about 10 minutes on foot.” I walk and see the park. It’s big and beautiful. I enjoy walking and taking pictures there.

Story 3: Tokyo
Hi, I’m Emma. In Tokyo, I want to go to a sushi restaurant. I ask a shopkeeper, “How do I get to Sushi Street?” She says, “Go left, then right, and it’s near the train station.” I follow her directions and find the restaurant. The sushi is delicious!

Story 4: Rome
Hello, I’m Emma. In Rome, I want to visit the Colosseum. I ask a man, “How can I get to the Colosseum?” He says, “Take bus number 75 and get off at the Colosseo stop.” I take the bus, and it’s easy to find. The Colosseum is incredible and full of history.

seo.metaTitle: Ordering Food and Drinks (Gọi món ăn và đồ uống)
seo.metaDescription: Thực sử dụng các mẫu câu đơn giản để hỏi và trả lời.

IF.IFname: Ordering Food and Drinks (Gọi món ăn và đồ uống)
IF.IFdes:
Story 1: Alice
Hi, I’m Alice. Today, I go to a café with my friend. I ask the waiter, “Can I have a cappuccino, please?” My friend orders a green tea. The waiter says, “Anything else?” I reply, “No, thank you.” After a few minutes, we get our drinks. The cappuccino is hot and delicious.

Story 2: Ben
Hello, I’m Ben. I visit a fast-food restaurant. I tell the cashier, “I’d like a cheeseburger and fries, please.” She asks, “What drink would you like?” I say, “A Coke, please.” She says, “That will be $8.” I pay and wait for my food. The meal is quick and tasty.

Story 3: Clara
Hi, I’m Clara. I go to a pizza restaurant with my family. I say, “I’d like a small pepperoni pizza, please.” The waiter asks, “Would you like a drink?” I reply, “Yes, an orange juice, please.” My family orders different pizzas. We enjoy eating together and sharing the food.

Story 4: Tom
Hello, I’m Tom. I go to an Italian restaurant for dinner. I say, “Can I have spaghetti with meatballs, please?” The waiter asks, “Would you like anything to drink?” I say, “Yes, a glass of water, please.” The food comes quickly, and it’s delicious. I thank the waiter before leaving.

IF.IFdes:
Story 1: Doctor’s Appointment
Hi, I’m Emma. I feel sick, so I call the clinic. I say, “Hello, I’d like to make an appointment with the doctor.” The receptionist asks, “When would you like to come?” I say, “Tomorrow morning, please.” She replies, “The doctor is free at 10:00 AM.” I say, “That’s perfect. Thank you!”

Story 2: Dentist Appointment
Hello, I’m Emma. I need to see the dentist. I call the dental clinic and say, “Can I book an appointment?” The receptionist asks, “What day works for you?” I reply, “Wednesday afternoon, please.” She says, “We have a spot at 3:00 PM.” I confirm, “That’s fine. Thank you!”

Story 3: Job Interview
Hi, I’m Emma. I get an email about a job interview. I reply, “Thank you for the opportunity. Can we schedule the interview for next Monday?” The manager replies, “Sure, let’s meet at 2:00 PM in our office.” I respond, “Great! I will be there. Thank you!”

Story 4: Hair Salon Appointment
Hello, I’m Emma. I need a haircut, so I call the salon. I say, “Can I make an appointment for a haircut?” The staff asks, “What time do you prefer?” I reply, “Saturday morning, please.” She says, “We have an opening at 9:30 AM.” I say, “Perfect. Thank you!”

IF.IFname: Talking About Weather (Nói về thời tiết)
IF.IFdes:
Story 1: Sunny Day
Hi, I’m Emma. Today is sunny and warm. The sky is blue, and there are no clouds. I say to my friend, “It’s a perfect day for a picnic!” She replies, “Yes, let’s go to the park.” We bring food and enjoy the sunshine. I love sunny weather.

Story 2: Rainy Day
Hello, I’m Emma. It’s raining today, so I take my umbrella. I say to my neighbor, “It’s a wet day!” He says, “Yes, it’s raining a lot this week.” I stay inside, drink tea, and read a book. Rainy days are quiet and relaxing for me.

Story 3: Snowy Day
Hi, I’m Emma. Today, it’s snowing! The ground is white, and the air is very cold. I say to my brother, “Let’s build a snowman!” He says, “Great idea!” We play in the snow and take pictures. Snowy weather makes me happy, but I wear a warm coat.

Story 4: Windy Day
Hello, I’m Emma. It’s very windy today. The trees are moving, and the air feels cool. I say to my mom, “It’s so windy outside!” She replies, “Be careful if you go out.” I wear my jacket and go for a short walk. Windy days are good for flying kites.

seo.metaTitle: Talking About Work or School (Nói về công việc hoặc trường học)
seo.metaDescription: Thực sử dụng các mẫu câu đơn giản để hỏi và trả lời.

IF.IFname: Talking About Work or School (Nói về công việc hoặc trường học)
IF.IFdes:
Story 1: Sarah (Work)
Hi, I’m Sarah. I work as a nurse at a hospital. I start work at 8:00 AM and finish at 5:00 PM. I take care of patients and help the doctors. My job is busy, but I love it because I help people. On weekends, I rest and spend time with my family.

Story 2: John (Work)
Hello, I’m John. I am a taxi driver. I drive people around the city every day. I start work early in the morning and finish at night. I enjoy meeting new people and talking with them. My favorite part of the job is driving along the beach road at sunset.

Story 3: Emma (School)
Hi, I’m Emma. I am a student at high school. I study English, math, and science. My favorite subject is English because I like learning new words. After school, I do my homework and play badminton with my friends. I want to be an English teacher in the future.

Story 4: Alex (School)
Hello, I’m Alex. I study at university. I am in my second year, and I study engineering. My classes start at 9:00 AM and finish at 3:00 PM. I enjoy building small machines in the lab. After class, I go to the library to read books about technology.

seo.metaTitle: Making Small Talk (Nói chuyện xã giao)
seo.metaDescription: Thực sử dụng các mẫu câu đơn giản để hỏi và trả lời.

IF.IFname: Making Small Talk (Nói chuyện xã giao)
IF.IFdes:
Story 1: At the Park
Hi, I’m Emma. Today, I meet a new neighbor at the park. I say, “Hi, the weather is so nice today!” She smiles and replies, “Yes, it’s sunny and perfect for a walk.” We talk about the trees and flowers in the park. She says, “Do you come here often?” I reply, “Yes, every morning.”

Story 2: At the Café
Hello, I’m Emma. I go to a café and sit next to a friendly person. I say, “The coffee here is really good.” He replies, “Yes, I love it too. Do you come here often?” I say, “Yes, this is my favorite café.” We talk about our favorite drinks and books.

Story 3: At the Train Station
Hi, I’m Emma. I’m waiting for my train and talk to a traveler next to me. I say, “Is this your first time here?” He replies, “Yes, I’m visiting for work.” I ask, “Where are you from?” He says, “I’m from Canada.” We talk about his trip, and he says he loves the city.

Story 4: At the Grocery Store
Hello, I’m Emma. At the grocery store, I meet an old friend. I say, “Hi! Long time no see!” She replies, “Yes, it’s been a while. How are you?” I say, “I’m good. How about you?” We talk about our families and what we are buying. She says, “Let’s catch up soon!” I agree.

seo.metaTitle: Health and Visiting the Doctor (Sức khỏe và đi khám bệnh)
seo.metaDescription: Thực sử dụng các mẫu câu đơn giản để hỏi và trả lời.

IF.IFname: Health and Visiting the Doctor (Sức khỏe và đi khám bệnh)
IF.IFdes:
Story 1: Mom
Hi, I’m Emma’s mom. I have a headache today, so I go to the doctor. I say, “I feel pain in my head, and it doesn’t go away.” The doctor asks, “Did you sleep well?” I say, “No, I didn’t.” He gives me medicine and says, “Rest and drink lots of water.”

Story 2: Dad
Hello, I’m Emma’s dad. My back hurts after working in the garden. I visit the clinic and say, “My back hurts when I move.” The doctor says, “You should avoid heavy lifting and rest for a few days.” She gives me cream to help with the pain. I feel better soon.

Story 3: Brother
Hi, I’m Emma’s brother. I have a fever, so my mom takes me to the doctor. I say, “I feel very hot and tired.” The doctor checks my temperature and says, “You have a fever. Drink lots of water and take this medicine.” After a few days, I feel healthy again.

Story 4: Grandma
Hello, I’m Emma’s grandma. I feel dizzy and go to the hospital. I say, “I feel lightheaded when I stand up.” The doctor asks, “Are you eating well?” I say, “Not much.” He tells me to eat healthy food and drink juice. I follow his advice and feel stronger.

seo.metaTitle: Travel and Transportation (Du lịch và phương tiện giao thông)
seo.metaDescription: Thực sử dụng các mẫu câu đơn giản để hỏi và trả lời.

IF.IFname: Travel and Transportation (Du lịch và phương tiện giao thông)
IF.IFdes:
Story 1: Paris
Hi, I’m Emma. I am traveling to Paris by train. At the station, I ask, “What time does the train to Paris leave?” The staff says, “It leaves at 9:30 AM.” I buy a ticket and wait on the platform. The train ride is fast and comfortable. I can’t wait to see the Eiffel Tower!

Story 2: New York
Hello, I’m Emma. In New York, I take a taxi to visit Times Square. I ask the driver, “How long will it take to get there?” He says, “About 20 minutes.” The city is busy with traffic, but the lights and buildings are amazing. I enjoy the ride and take lots of pictures.

Story 3: Tokyo
Hi, I’m Emma. In Tokyo, I take the subway to visit Shibuya Crossing. At the ticket machine, I ask a local, “Which line goes to Shibuya?” She says, “Take the green line.” I follow her advice and arrive in 15 minutes. The subway is clean and very fast.

Story 4: Rome
Hello, I’m Emma. In Rome, I rent a bicycle to explore the city. I ask the shopkeeper, “How much is it to rent a bike for a day?” He says, “It’s $15.” I ride to the Colosseum and enjoy the view. Biking is a fun way to see the streets of Rome.

seo.metaTitle: Talking About Celebrations and Festivals (Nói về các dịp lễ và lễ hội)
seo.metaDescription: Thực sử dụng các mẫu câu đơn giản để hỏi và trả lời.

IF.IFname: Talking About Celebrations and Festivals (Nói về các dịp lễ và lễ hội)
IF.IFdes:
Story 1: Christmas
Hi, I’m Emma. My family loves Christmas. We decorate the tree with lights and ornaments. On Christmas Eve, we have a big dinner with turkey and cake. In the morning, we open gifts together. I love spending time with my family during this special holiday. It is full of joy and love.

Story 2: New Year’s Eve
Hello, I’m Emma. On New Year’s Eve, I celebrate with my friends. We watch fireworks at midnight. Before that, we have a party with snacks and music. Everyone says, “Happy New Year!” when the clock strikes 12. I make a wish and plan my goals for the new year.

Story 3: Halloween
Hi, I’m Emma. Halloween is so much fun! I dress up as a witch and go to a party with my friends. We carve pumpkins and play games. Kids come to our door and say, “Trick or treat!” We give them candy. The costumes and decorations make Halloween exciting.

Story 4: Birthday
Hello, I’m Emma. My birthday is in June. This year, my family throws me a small party at home. I blow out candles on a chocolate cake and make a wish. My friends give me gifts and sing “Happy Birthday.” We play games and take photos. It’s a wonderful day.
